ygData.subject: RE: Psalm of Cooling & testing out CoD and DDD
ygData.msgSnippet: I used the song all the time in HighKeep since I got it (now lvl 35 hell). It is a cool song but I did not see that I get ultravision at all. On another note,
ygData.messageBody:
I used the song all the time in HighKeep since I got it (now lvl 35 hell).
It is a cool song but I did not see that I get ultravision at all.

On another note, last night I tested out CoD and DDD on my guildmates lvl 39
cleric.

All of this was with instruments.

CoD - 19, 10, 10 = 39dmg in 10 seconds
DDD - 20, 10, 10 = 40dmg in 10 seconds

Skill in each instrument is max at my lvl of 35.

Your Friendly Rogue and Bard
Hammerpaw and Syren Wind
Champions of Norrath, The Rathe


-----Original Message-----
From: kim@... [mailto:kim@...]
Sent: Thursday, September 09, 1999 12:01 PM
To: eqbards@onelist.com
Subject: [eqbards] Psalm of Cooling


From: <kim@...>

I played around with Psalm of Cooling (L33) briefly in
Runnyeye last night and immediately noticed that it also
grants ultravision.

Unfortunately I had to put it away as it was just me and a
paladin exploring deep inside Runnyeye and I needed every song
slot. I didn't get to use it in combat. Has anyone used this
song extensively?

--
John H. Kim
